This paper deals with the computational complexity of model checking for dynamic epistemic logic, which is a logical framework for representing and reasoning about knowledge change for multiple agents. This topic is closely related to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on formal logic and computational complexity, cs.LO and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
